        "name": "[P1] Intercom Incident : Razed Production",
        "status": "Closed",
        "reported_at": "2026-06-08T14:57:17Z",
        "permalink": "https://app.incident.io/fasttrack-solutions/incidents/9139",
        "summary": "Problem: Customers in the Razed Production environment were blocked from launching or editing CRM lifecycles due to a frontend error caused by segments with incorrect categories.\n\nImpact: Customers in the Razed Production environment were unable to launch or edit CRM lifecycles, which prevented them from managing campaigns until the fix was deployed. No other brands were impacted after a global SQL check confirmed all other environments were unaffected.\n\nCauses: A bug in the crm-api caused segments to be assigned the wrong category when cloning lifecycles. This resulted in the frontend filtering out required segments and blocking lifecycle launches.\n\nSteps to resolve: We identified segments with the wrong category and manually updated them. A fix was deployed to crm-api to ensure cloned lifecycles receive the correct segment category. A global SQL check confirmed only Razed Production was impacted. The fix will roll out to other brands through the normal stable release process. The partner confirmed the issue is resolved as of 6:08pm CEST."
      }
